ANG</b>."<BR>AND THERE WAS <b>WANG</b><BR>AND GOD SAID,<br>"IT IS GOOD."<br>AND IT WAS GOOD<BR><br><br>"Every problem in the universe can be solved by finding the right long-haired prettyboy and beating the crap out of him." <i>- Rule 116, <a href="http://guardian.simplenet.com/text/rpg.html">CRPG Rule List</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/20/01 10:46:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=459.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm.</span><hr size=1> They are pretty powerful at the moment.<br><br><br>In my opinion, though, the cancel magic bug WILL get fixed, it basically has to be.  The combination of that, and everyone's gradually increasing resistances will shove the druids back down.  Remember where they rank on a mature PVP server... not so high.  <br><br>Dr00ds are (in my experience) being most effective as solo or duo raiders in a big zone like LOIO.  A few responsible citizens have to form a posse, and the druid is either driven out, gates, hides with lev over the lake, or whatever.  Tonight a pickup group I was in ran off a druid, a mage, and some other caster that gated before I could find out its class.  <br><br>Against a group of evens and greens, these wandering druids can hide away at worst, wasting our time.  If they come into casting range to fight some, someone will eventualy land a dark and they'll be dead if they can't gate.<br><br>I'm no longer that worried in LOIO soloing, I just stay near other people.  These types just want a few points from a lone soloist, they won't risk a real fight.<br><br>When I hit 39 and the cancel magic/resistance bugs are fixed, I won't be too concerned about near-con druids 1on1.  What do they have for unresistable firepower besides good dots?  <br><br>And don't forget, those damage shields have pretty short durations and very high mana costs.  They can't keep them up forever.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MARBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 3:28:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=459.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm.</span><hr size=1> Currently this is what they usuaully have up in pvp and you cant dispell<br><br>Damage shield <br>Sow<br>See invis<br>Magic, cold, fire resists (maybe others)<br>Levitate<br><br>Now as a rogue, and usually a snared one when they spot me, how the heck am I supposed to get by that if I can't pumice them?<br><br>But I try, and I try, and I die, and I die, I can't get no.....satisfaction....<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Martyrdom is too cool<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 5:52:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=459.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cancel Magic</span><hr size=1> The cancel magic bug will HAVE to be fixed soon unless Verant wants SZers casting Sp